Bebe Daniels https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bebe_Daniels 0 Phyllis Virginia "Bebe" Daniels (January 14, 1901 – March 16, 1971) was an American actress, singer, dancer, writer and producer. She began her career in Hollywood during the silent film era as a child actress, became a star in musicals such as 42nd Street, and later gained further fame on radio and television in Britain. In a long career, Daniels appeared in 230 films. Phyllis_Virginia_"_Bebe_"_Daniels ( January_14_,_1901 – March_16_,_1971 ) was an_American_actress , singer , dancer , writer_and_producer .
